  "text": "where υ ∈ (0, 1/2] denotes the violation probability threshold which is a system design parameter controlling the desired level of conservatism. Remark that the SINR requirement γ k translates to an achievable target rate of R k = log 2 (1 + γ k ), under ergodic conditions on the channel [CITATION_1] . Therefore, the constraint (8) can also be read as a rate-outage probability constraint, ensuring that the transmission rate R k is achievable for the kth user with probability (at least) 1 − υ. For the sake of notation, we denote the stochastic uncertain component of the CI constraint by",
